ing=1><TR><TD valign=top BACKGROUND= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/tableBackground.gif><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top BACKGROUND= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/tableBackground.gif><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#aaaaaa><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/urealcool23.showPublicProfile?language=EN>realcool23</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www16.brinkster.com/realcool23/cg1tp.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Karbonite</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>4/9/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>9:04:23 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www16.brinkster.com/realcool23/blaster.gif width=120 lenght=210 alt='Bam! http://brads.cjb.net Bam!'></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Inking Q...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">When you ink what do u use to ink? A pen or a maker or what? say you use a micron, so u use just one micron or do you vary the widths (change to a different width) as you draw?<br>
<br>
any answers would be apreciated.<br>
<br>
-brad</font><P><a href="http://brads.cjb.net"><IMG SRC="http://www16.brinkster.com/realcool23/banners/mine.jpg" ALT="Studio IndEX" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=40 BORDER=2></a><br>This <i> isnt'</i> your <b>grandmas</b> Art!!!<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CCCCCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/upuhead.showPublicProfile?language=EN>puhead</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Karbonite</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>4/10/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>8:33:35 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://pu.mordea.com/misc/bbsicon03.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Inking Q...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I use all sorts of different widths and pens.<br>
I use a brush pen, 005, 01, and 08 sakura micron.<br>
Plus a sharpie marker for complete black areas.<br>
<br>
Adding line width is useful when conveying a sense of depth to an unshaded piece of lineart.</font><P><font face=verdana size=2><a href=http://pu.mordea.com><img src="http://pu.mordea.com/banners/ta_banner01.jpg" width="200" height="40" border="0" alt="visit my site! ^_^"></a><br>
**under constant construction**
</font><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#aaaaaa><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=firestorm>FireStorm</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Pre-Karbonite</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>4/10/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>5:29:56 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Inking Q...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">When I ink, I mostly use a sable hair brush.  I find that it makes your lines smoother than a pen does.  I also think the art itself looks better when inked with a brush.<br>
<br>
Simba says roar.<br>
<br>
